H0.text: In electromagnetism, which unit is found by multiplying volts by amperes. Joules

H1.text: In electromagnetism, which unit is found by multiplying volts by amperes. Ohms

H2.text: In electromagnetism, which unit is found by multiplying volts by amperes. Coulombs

H3.text: In electromagnetism, which unit is found by multiplying volts by amperes. Watts

A5.text: In terms of electromagnetism, one watt is the rate at which electrical work is performed when a current of one ampere flows across an electrical potential difference of one volt.
